---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base title="Projects">
  <h1>Projects</h1>
  <p class="subtitle">Systems I build, from product work to personal infrastructure.</p>

  <div class="project" id="sleephub">
    <h3>SleepHub</h3>
    <span class="tag">product</span>
    <span class="tag">ambient AI</span>
    <span class="tag">voice agents</span>
    <p>
      Bedside AI system for autonomous sleep coaching and monitoring at
      <a href="https://asleep.ai">Asleep</a>.
      Combines contactless sleep sensing with voice interaction and personalized health insights.
      Not just an app -- an ambient, autonomous product that works while you sleep.
    </p>
    <p>
      This is the anchor project: real product work where agent infrastructure,
      voice AI, and applied ML converge into something people use every night.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="project" id="knowledge-os">
    <h3>Knowledge OS</h3>
    <span class="tag">personal OS</span>
    <span class="tag">markdown-first</span>
    <span class="tag">agent memory</span>
    <p>
      A private, agent-native personal operating system built around a markdown-first knowledge layer.
      Turns scattered context -- notes, GitHub, email, conversations -- into structured,
      reusable task context for agents and humans alike.
    </p>
    <p>
      Architecture: raw sources ingested into compiled wiki pages (topics, projects, people, decisions),
      with schema rules governing maintenance and retrieval.
      This site is the first public layer derived from it --
      curated public expression on top of private memory, not a raw dump.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="project" id="agent-infra">
    <h3>Agent Infrastructure</h3>
    <span class="tag">runtime</span>
    <span class="tag">agent control</span>
    <span class="tag">harness engineering</span>
    <p>
      Tooling and patterns for making agents reliable enough to trust with real workflows.
      Focused on structured agent control -- treating agents as stateful sessions
      that can be resumed, steered, and automated, not just prompted.
    </p>
    <p>
      Covers runtime correctness, memory continuity, evaluation loops,
      session lifecycle management, and the harness engineering that makes
      the same underlying model dramatically more useful.
      Includes work on CLI adapters, context packaging, and agent-native workflow tooling.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="project" id="utilities">
    <h3>Utilities and Experiments</h3>
    <span class="tag">tools</span>
    <span class="tag">automation</span>
    <span class="tag">glue</span>
    <p>
      Small, concrete tools that reduce real workflow friction --
      CLI adapters, infra glue, environment management, interaction-layer experiments.
      Shipping energy expressed as practical tool-making.
    </p>
    <p>
      These are not side noise. They are part of the same builder identity:
      dotfiles as real infrastructure, adapters as interface bridges,
      and small repos as signals of how systems get stitched together in practice.
    </p>
  </div>
</Base>
